## Agents

This repo uses a Claude Code agent system managed by CCAutomated:

| Agent | Role |
|-------|------|
| Researcher | Codebase analysis and exploration. Read-only. |
| Implementer | Implements features, fixes bugs. Uses stack-specific tools. |
| Reviewer | Reviews code quality, security, correctness. Read-only. |
| Mutagen | Evolution engine. Discovers new tools, prunes unused ones, creates skills. |
| Mutagen Discovery | Web scout. Searches for new plugins/MCP servers on session start. |

## Mutagen Evolution

The Mutagen agent runs on every session start. It is **advisory-only** — it never applies changes without your approval.

On session start, Mutagen:
- Reads its memory (`.claude/mutagen-memory/`) for past evaluations and decisions
- Analyzes usage patterns for pruning candidates, skill opportunities, and efficiency improvements
- Searches for new relevant plugins and MCP servers (skips already-evaluated ones)
- For high-frequency tools (10+ uses), searches for faster alternatives
- Detects bash-to-builtin opportunities (e.g., `grep -r` → Grep tool)
- Writes all findings to `.claude/mutagen-memory/pending-recommendations.md`
- Greets you with a summary of recommendations (silent if nothing to report)

Respond with "approve all", "approve 1,3", "reject 2", "details 1", or "skip" to defer to next session.
